  "category_subtitle": "Learn how to count books and bound volumes in Japanese using 冊",
  "category_detail": "<b>Counting Books in Japanese</b><br><br>In Japanese, books and bound printed materials are counted using the counter <b>「冊」(さつ / satsu)</b>.<br><br>This counter is commonly used for <b>books, notebooks, magazines, dictionaries, manuals, and other bound publications</b>.<br><br><b>Important Sound Changes</b><br>Some numbers change pronunciation when combined with 冊.<br><br><span class=\"example\">1冊</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(いっさつ / issatsu)</span><br><span class=\"example\">8冊</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(はっさつ / hassatsu)</span><br><span class=\"example\">10冊</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(じゅっさつ / jussatsu)</span><br><br><b>Common Usage</b><br><span class=\"example\">本を三冊買いました。</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(hon o sansatsu kaimashita)</span><br>Meaning: I bought three books.<br><br>This counter is very commonly used in everyday life and when shopping for books.",
